Hello! It's me in my studio on a rainy day :) thanks for being here and following my little art journey and supporting me in all the different ways. It will be five years of fulltime freelance and sometimes I wonder how I made it at all!?

One of my goals this year is to start playing more with texture and looseness to try an keep the energy of my sketches in the final pieces.

With this one, I was inspired by one of my favorite things - @dance_church. DC is more than a time to dance and “workout,” it’s a place where I’ve learned that I am worthy of the space I take up. Also, just shaking my ass with friends/strangers whose names I don’t know but would recognize them on a dance floor anytime is pretty much something I never knew I would come to rely on for my wellbeing. Love you, Dance Church!

Channeling Charley Harper with this piece 〰️🐟 If you're not familiar with Harper, I suggest you take a peek! He was an American artist with an insane minimal style that distilled shapes, layers and colors into beautiful illustrations of the natural word. His work was super inspiring while I was studying printmaking and trying to learn about incorporating texture into my work. And, texture is an art goal of mine this year, so I'm happy to revisit an old fave artist.

Happy International Women's Day to ALL HUMANS WHO IDENTIFY AS WOMEN. I am proud to have gotten to create this artwork for The Kraken! Protecting the rights of our trans siblings to compete, play, and even just exist in public safely is a responsibility that I take seriously and I hope you’ll join me!
Thank you so much to every person who has reached out and celebrated this fun work with me! It's so appreciated and I feel so empowered as an artist. Getting to use this little platform of mine is a huge opportunity to share what is important. Not all inequality is created equally - the work is not done!

Everything isn't fine. We're watching the world unravel on our phones. I've been carrying a lot of guilt for sharing my flowers and other art, while we're scrolling past death and pain and destruction. Watching artists I look up to go another day without amplifying the voices of Palestinians only increased my trepidation - fear of institutional punishment, making mistakes, being accused of anti-semitism and comments and DMs gives me so much anxiety. But I can't care about that anymore. I'm not a quiet person and the shame the US has brought the world is unbearable. If you've been scared to speak up, take this as a sign to do it. Protect those who can't protect themselves, amplify the journalists publishing the truth! Ceasefire now. #freepalestine #ceasefire #ceasefirenow

Toaster. Tostito. Toad. Toadstool.  Babycat. After 17 years my grumpy lil dude left this Earth yesterday, three days before my birthday. Dash and I were supposed to be in Portugal but due to other issues, we had to cancel. I have to believe some cosmic forces shaped the plans for me to be here for Toaster.

I reluctantly adopted Toaster in Baltimore when I was 19; I had no experience with cats and was honestly kind of scared of them. In 16 years together, he showed me infinite sweetness and loyalty. If you ever met Toaster he probably ignored you or swat at you. He was the ultimate curmudgeon. Our connection made me feel like a witch with her familiar. I was his person.

Watching Toast grow from a young cat to a super-senior was an honor. I'll miss watching him sunbathe in beams of light, yapping at me for myriad reasons, his aggressive purring and drooly headbutts, showing off to guests by picking him up and stretching him out like a prize pig, his warm squishy old cat belly, and knowing he'd be at the door when I came home.

You're in my heart forever, Toaster.
Maybe my messy handwriting will help? Just learned about this and thought I'd share!

🇵🇸
